<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,892,992]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lee, Corbari &amp; Richer de Forges, 2015: 1258 -" authorityYear="1262" box="[189,420,892,918]" class="Malacostraca" family="Epialtidae" genus="Oxypleurodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="forte">
<emphasis box="[189,420,892,918]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Oxypleurodon forte</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected on seamounts in the middle of the SCS during the NANHAI 2014 cruise (
<bibRefCitation author="Lee" box="[276,462,928,955]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Lee" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1255 - 1263" refId="ref16199" refString="Lee B. Y., Corbari L. &amp; Richer de Forges B. 2015. Deep-sea spider crabs of the genus Oxypleurodon Miers, 1885 (Decapoda, Brachyura, Majoidea, Epialtidae), from the NANHAI 2014 cruise in the South China Sea, with a description of a new species. Crustaceana 88 (12 - 14): 1255 - 1263. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 15685403 - 00003488" type="journal article" year="2015">
Lee 
<emphasis box="[330,383,929,955]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
). The new series of small specimens collected during ZHONGSHA shows that the species has a wider distribution in the SCS.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
